  "title": "Cricothyroidotomy and tracheostomy",
  "body_html": "<b>Cricothyroidotomy</b><br /><ul><li>Involves creating an airway via the space between thyroid and cricoid cartilages</li><li>The skin, subcutaneous connective tissue and median cricothyroid ligament are divided to establish the airway.</li><li>Can be performed either with scalpel incision or needle methods.</li><li>For establishing airway in short term.</li></ul><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti551b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti551.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'></td><td align='right'></td></tr></table></CENTER><div class='imagetext'>Cricothyroidotomy is a stoma made by incising the cricothyroid membrame (ligament) which lies between the thyroid and cricoid cartilages. Tracheostomy is typically made by incising between the 2nd and 3rd tracheal rings</div><br /><b>Tracheostomy</b><br /><ul><li>A cricothyroidotomy will typically be converted to a tracheostomy if there is a longer term need for an airway here.</li><li>Often performed in theatre rather than emergency setting but knowledge is required</li><li>Typically placed between 2nd and 3rd tracheal rings but may be a level above or below.</li></ul></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodylinks\"><table style='width:100%'><tr><td>BJA education</td><td style = \"float: right;width:115px;\"><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"link_like_63\" data-linkid=\"63\" data-rating=\"1\" class=\"rate-link btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-up\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-up\"/></svg></button><span id=\"link_good_count_63\" class = \"link_good_count\" style=\"color:green; font-size:85%;\">0</span><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"link_dislike_63\" data-linkid=\"63\" data-rating=\"0\" class=\"rate-link btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-down\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-down\"/></svg></button><span id=\"link_bad_count_63\" class = \"link_bad_count\" style=\"color:red; font-size:85%;\">0</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://academic.oup.com/bjaed/article/14/6/268/247676\">Tracheostomy</a></td></tr></table><br><br><table style='width:100%'><tr><td>Anaesthesia UK</td><td style = \"float: right;width:115px;\"><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"link_like_64\" data-linkid=\"64\" data-rating=\"1\" class=\"rate-link btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-up\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-up\"/></svg></button><span id=\"link_good_count_64\" class = \"link_good_count\" style=\"color:green; font-size:85%;\">0</span><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"link_dislike_64\" data-linkid=\"64\" data-rating=\"0\" class=\"rate-link btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-down\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-down\"/></svg></button><span id=\"link_bad_count_64\" class = \"link_bad_count\" style=\"color:red; font-size:85%;\">0</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.frca.co.uk/article.aspx?articleid=243\">Tracheostomy</a></td></tr></table></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodymedia\"></div>\n\n\n<div id=\"categorynum\">1</div>\n\n<div id=\"subcategorynum\">2</div>\n\n<div id=\"categoryname\">Anatomy</div>\n\n<div id=\"subcategoryname\">Head & neck anatomy</div>\n<div id=\"mybody\">\n\n<div id=\"body_content\">\n<b>Cricothyroidotomy</b><br /><ul><li>Involves creating an airway via the space between thyroid and cricoid cartilages</li><li>The skin, subcutaneous connective tissue and median cricothyroid ligament are divided to establish the airway.</li><li>Can be performed either with scalpel incision or needle methods.</li><li>For establishing airway in short term.</li></ul><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti551b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti551.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'></td><td align='right'></td></tr></table></CENTER><div class='imagetext'>Cricothyroidotomy is a stoma made by incising the cricothyroid membrame (ligament) which lies between the thyroid and cricoid cartilages. Tracheostomy is typically made by incising between the 2nd and 3rd tracheal rings</div><br /><b>Tracheostomy</b><br /><ul><li>A cricothyroidotomy will typically be converted to a tracheostomy if there is a longer term need for an airway here.</li><li>Often performed in theatre rather than emergency setting but knowledge is required</li><li>Typically placed between 2nd and 3rd tracheal rings but may be a level above or below.</li></ul></div>\n\n\n<BR><BR><table style='width:100%'><tr><td>BJA education</td><td style = \"float: right;width:115px;\"><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"link_like_63\" data-linkid=\"63\" data-rating=\"1\" class=\"rate-link btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-up\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-up\"/></svg></button><span id=\"link_good_count_63\" class = \"link_good_count\" style=\"color:green; font-size:85%;\">0</span><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"link_dislike_63\" data-linkid=\"63\" data-rating=\"0\" class=\"rate-link btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-down\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-down\"/></svg></button><span id=\"link_bad_count_63\" class = \"link_bad_count\" style=\"color:red; font-size:85%;\">0</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://academic.oup.com/bjaed/article/14/6/268/247676\">Tracheostomy</a></td></tr></table><br><br><table style='width:100%'><tr><td>Anaesthesia UK</td><td style = \"float: right;width:115px;\"><button type=\"button\" style=\"